rules.title: Business apps must always require login
rules.description: No anonymous means every user must have valid login session or credentials
rules.remediation: Disable anonymous/guest access in Project Security

rules.title: Business apps should disable demo users
rules.description: No demo users
rules.remediation: Disable demo users in Project Security

rules.title: Strong password policy
rules.description: Bruteforce is quite common. Ensure passwords are very strong.
rules.remediation: Ensure minimum password length of at least 8 characters and must use all character classes.

rules.title: Administrator username must be 'MxRADmin'
rules.description: Project security must be configured so that the administrator username equals 'MxRADmin'.
rules.remediation: Set the username of the administrator user to 'MxRADmin'.

rules.title: Default time zones must be 'Europe/Amsterdam'
rules.description: Project settings must be configured so that both the default time zone and the scheduled event time zone equal 'Europe/Amsterdam'.
rules.remediation: Set both 'DefaultTimeZoneCode' and 'ScheduledEventTimeZoneCode' in the project settings to 'Europe/Amsterdam'.

rules.title: Check security option must be enabled
rules.description: Project settings must be configured so that the 'CheckSecurity' option is enabled.
rules.remediation: Enable the 'Check security' option in the project security.

rules.title: Security level must be 'Production'
rules.description: Project security must be configured so that the 'Security level' option equals 'Production'.
rules.remediation: Set the 'Security level' option in the project security to 'Production'.

rules.title: Strict page URL check must be enabled
rules.description: Project security must be configured so that the 'Strict page URL check' option is enabled.
rules.remediation: Enable the 'Strict page URL check' option in the project security.

rules.title: Inherit from Administration.Account
rules.description: There is no need to inherit from administration.account. Administration.account may simply be extended, this is not a system module. Avoid unnecessary inheritance as this has a negative effect on performance.
rules.remediation: Inherit from system.user instead or adapt Administration.Account so it fits your needs.

rules.title: Inherit from non System module is discouraged
rules.description: Inheritance, except from system module, is strongly discouraged because of the negative performance side effects.
rules.remediation: Instead of inheritance, just use separate objects which are associated to the main object. As an alternative, you can add the childs attributes to the super entity and add an ObjectType enumeration.

rules.title: Avoid using system storage objects directly
rules.description: Always inherit for filedocuments and images. Never implement direct assocations to the System Domain Model, because of limits on the configuration of security.
rules.remediation: Remove direct associations with the System Domain Model. Use inheritance instead (i.e. Generalization in the entity properties).

rules.title: Avoid using validation rules for domain model.
rules.description: Validation rules on domain model level will give the users unexpected errors.
rules.remediation: Remove datamodel validation rules.

rules.title: Avoid using default read write access
rules.description: This can lead to wrong set access rights
rules.remediation: Set default access rights to Read only or None.

rules.title: Persistable entities should not have create and delete rights
rules.description: Persistable entities in the domain model must not expose create or delete rights directly in the client.
rules.remediation: Remove create and delete rights from persistable entities and use these operations only through the Mendix runtime.

rules.title: Entities should not use calculated attributes
rules.description: Domain model entities must not define attributes with a calculated value.
rules.remediation: Replace calculated attributes with stored attributes, and calculate their values using microflows, nanoflows, or during data retrieval instead.

rules.title: Linguistic naming: Boolean-like names must use Boolean type
rules.description: Detecteert lingustische naamgevingsfouten, zoals boolean-achtige namen met ander datatype. Attribute names that suggest a boolean value (e.g., Is*, Has*, Can*, Heeft*, etc.) must use BooleanAttributeType.
rules.remediation: Either rename the attribute to not suggest a boolean value, or change the attribute type to Boolean.

rules.title: More than 20 modules in project
rules.description: The bigger the application, the harder to maintain.
rules.remediation: Consider a multi-app stategy to avoid creating one big (unmaintainable) monstrous application.

rules.title: Inline style property used
rules.description: Avoid using the style property, because this will make the life of your UI designer a lot more complicated. It will be harder to overrule styles from CSS file level.
rules.remediation: Use generic classes instead, defined by the theme.

rules.title: Images must have alt text
rules.description: All images must have alt text so that screen readers can describe them
rules.remediation: Set an alt text for the image

rules.title: Buttons must not use 'No action'
rules.description: Flags buttons whose action is not specified.
rules.remediation: Configure a real action for the button (e.g. microflow, nanoflow, or page navigation) or remove the unused button.

rules.title: Widget data sources must start with 'DataSourceFor'
rules.description: Flags widget data source microflows and nanoflows whose name does not start with 'DataSourceFor'.
rules.remediation: Rename the microflow or nanoflow used as a widget data source so that its name starts with 'DataSourceFor' (e.g. 'DataSourceForMyGrid').

rules.title: Action button flows must start with 'On'
rules.description: Flags action buttons whose microflow or nanoflow name does not start with 'On'.
rules.remediation: Rename the associated microflow or nanoflow so that its name starts with 'On' (e.g. OnSave, OnClickSubmit) or remove the unused action.

rules.title: Empty String check not complete
rules.description: Technically, there is a difference between empty and "". Make sure to check them both.
rules.remediation: Always check a string for empty based on != empty and != "". The first one equals database NULL value, the latter one indicates a truncated string.

rules.title: Commit actions with a loop
rules.description: Commiting objects within a loop will fire a SQL Update query for each iteration.
rules.remediation: Consider committing objects outside the loop. Within the loop, add them to a list.

rules.title: No more than 25 elements in a microflow
rules.description: The bigger a microflow, the harder it will be to maintain.
rules.remediation: Split microflow into logical, functional elements.

rules.title: Variables in microflows and nanoflows must be PascalCase and meaningful
rules.description: Variables in microflows and nanoflows must use PascalCase naming and avoid single-letter names, acronyms, meaningless names and names ending with digits.
rules.remediation: Rename the variable so that its name is in PascalCase (e.g. 'MyVariableName'), is descriptive, does not end with digits and does not use acronyms or meaningless names.

rules.title: Avoid manual transaction management in microflows and nanoflows
rules.description: Microflows and nanoflows must not start or end transactions manually. Rely on Mendix's built-in transaction management instead of using CommunityCommons.StartTransaction or CommunityCommons.EndTransaction.
rules.remediation: Remove any manual transaction start or end Java actions (CommunityCommons.StartTransaction and CommunityCommons.EndTransaction) from microflows and nanoflows, and rely on Mendix's built-in transaction management instead.

rules.title: Avoid manual transaction management in microflows and nanoflows
rules.description: Microflows and nanoflows must not start or end transactions manually. Rely on Mendix's built-in transaction management instead of using CommunityCommons.StartTransaction or CommunityCommons.EndTransaction.
rules.remediation: Remove any manual transaction start or end Java actions (CommunityCommons.StartTransaction and CommunityCommons.EndTransaction) from microflows and nanoflows, and rely on Mendix's built-in transaction management instead.

rules.title: REST/HTTP endpoints must not use hardcoded IPs or hostnames
rules.description: Microflows REST and Web Service call actions must not contain hardcoded IP addresses or hostnames in their HTTP configuration (override location).
rules.remediation: Use a constant, configuration, or variable instead of hardcoded IP addresses or hostnames in HTTP override locations.

rules.title: Object and list variables must be checked for empty/null before use
rules.description: In Mendix 10 microflows and nanoflows, object and list variables (including parameters) must be checked for empty/null before they are used. This rule scans expressions and non-expression variable references (e.g. ChangeVariableName, DeleteVariableName, etc.) and only enforces checks on variables that are actually used.
rules.remediation: Before using an object or list variable, make sure you check it for empty (for example, `$MyObject != empty` or `$MyCount > 0` for list counts) in an exclusive split or equivalent logic.

rules.title: User interaction is not allowed in data source microflows and nanoflows
rules.description: In data source microflows and nanoflows (names starting with 'DataSourceFor'), user interaction activities are not allowed. This rule scans all action activities in such microflows/nanoflows and reports an error when a user interaction activity is used (for example Show Page, Show Message, Call Nanoflow, or Synchronize with Server).
rules.remediation: Remove user interaction activities from data source microflows and nanoflows. Move any required user interaction (such as showing pages, messages, or calling nanoflows/JavaScript actions) to a separate microflow/nanoflow that is triggered by the UI, and keep data source microflows/nanoflows focused on data retrieval and processing only.

rules.title: Expression is always true or false
rules.description: Detects Mendix expressions that are constant and always evaluate to true or false (for example 'true = true', '1 = 1', '1 < 0'). Such expressions usually indicate dead branches or mistakes in conditions.
rules.remediation: Review and refactor expressions that are always true or false. Replace them with a meaningful condition or remove the dead branch.

rules.title: Unused variables in microflows and nanoflows must be removed
rules.description: In microflows and nanoflows, variables that are never used should be deleted to keep flows clean and maintainable. This rule scans variable definitions (parameters, result variables, aggregate outputs, etc.) and reports any that are never referenced.
rules.remediation: Remove variables that are defined but never used, such as unused parameters, result variables of actions, or aggregate outputs. If the variable is intended to be used, add the missing logic that references it.

rules.title: Document names must be PascalCase
rules.description: Checks that the Name of a document is written in PascalCase.
rules.remediation: Rename the document so that its name is in PascalCase (e.g. 'MyDocumentName').

rules.title: Noqa directive must specify rule numbers
rules.description: Checks that #noqa directives in Documentation fields specify which rules to skip (e.g. #noqa:002_0001) rather than skipping all checks.
rules.remediation: Specify which rules to skip in the #noqa directive (e.g. '#noqa:002_0001' or '#noqa:002_0001,002_0002').

rules.title: Follow Rotterdam Code Architecture Conventions
rules.description: Checks that microflows, pages, and other elements are placed in the correct folder structure according to Rotterdam conventions.
rules.remediation: Move files to the correct folder according to the Rotterdam architecture conventions. See the project structure diagram for guidance.
